  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Timed Up and Go-test (TUG)in seconds.</measure>
    <time_frame>30 days</time_frame>
    <description>Timed Up and Go-test is performed when the patient is able to undertake the test after surgery. This is judged by a physiotherapist. The test measures how long it takes the patient to rise, walk 3 meters, turn around, walk back and sit down again.</description>
